Media notes: calling from low perch next to trail
Heard the bluebird-esque yewr and found the bird low in a foliage row. It started smacking more, seems likely alarmed. We backed off and kept pointing at it for a minute.

Locality: Clear Creek Natural Heritage Center, Denton
Behaviors: Call; Flight Call; Foraging or Eating

Media notes: Two call types, smack and descending whistle. Perhaps near nest?
